(Descirption)
Given two strings s and t, return true if t is an anagram of s, and false otherwise.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public boolean isAnagram(String s, String t) {
        char[] s_chars = s.toCharArray();
        char[] t_chars = t.toCharArray();

        Arrays.sort(s_chars);
        Arrays.sort(t_chars);

        return Arrays.equals(s_chars, t_chars);
    }
}

--- Approach ---
1. Converting strings to the Arrays, composed with chars.
2. Sorting the two Arrays.
- Anagram means that two words have same letters regardless their order.
3. Therefore, if they are anagram to each other, the two sorted Arrays should be same.
